3.0 of 5 bubbles
How to ruin a good beach.
Apr 2023 • Couples
I was very disappointed with the way this beach is over- managed. The life guards squeeze everyone into a very narrow section which make for an unnecessarily crowded experience and limits swimming and a sense of freedom. I would not stay here again.
Written April 17, 2023
Meuok
Bang Sare, Thailand150 contributions
AS GOOD AS A TOWN BEACH GETS....
Feb 2020 • Family
Contrary to certain other reviews, I found this beach to be pretty clean, and there wasn't much here that I could moan about.
In fact, my nine year old, insisted that she would enjoy a swim, especially if there were big breakers, between four and six every evening during our stay, and normally, to my chagrin, pulling me into the sea as well.
Safety would seem to be a big thing here, with about twenty or si lifeguards....
Written March 10, 2020
Jan 2024 • Family
My Khe is the central beach of Da Nang city. It's a long and sandy beach, pretty wide.
Many hotels line it, just across a busy street. There're many free parts, as well some where's a bar and where you can rent sunbeds. Water is shallow for long, usually with waves.
Try to get up early one day before sunrise, as the beach is east oriented. Apart beautiful scenery of the rising sun, you'll enjoy many locals around swimming, practicing tai-chi, jogging, exercising.
